🧮 Min And Operations – Java Solution
📌 Problem Summary

Given a set:

S = {0, 1, 2, ..., N}

Where N is even, repeatedly:

Remove two elements X and Y

Add max(X, Y) to score

Insert (X & Y) if not already present

Continue until only one element remains.

We must compute the minimum possible final score.

💡 Key Formula

For every test case:

Minimum Score = N × (N + 2) / 4

Since N is even, the result is always an integer.

🚀 Java Implementation
import java.io.BufferedReader;
import java.io.InputStreamReader;
import java.io.IOException;

public class MinAndOperations {

    public static void main(String[] args) throws IOException {
        BufferedReader br = new BufferedReader(new InputStreamReader(System.in));
        StringBuilder output = new StringBuilder();

        int T = Integer.parseInt(br.readLine().trim());

        while (T-- > 0) {
            long N = Long.parseLong(br.readLine().trim());

            // Using the derived formula
            long result = (N * (N + 2)) / 4;

            output.append(result).append("\n");
        }

        System.out.print(output);
    }
}
⏱ Complexity

Time Complexity: O(T)

Space Complexity: O(1)

Constraint-safe for:

1 ≤ T ≤ 100

1 ≤ N ≤ 5000
